    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-02T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-02T14:00:00-05:00" n="374"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A.R.–N.C./64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-02T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 2, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Department’s telegram No. 30, February 29, 9 p.m. The Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs has just informed me that the communication <pb facs="0303" n="291"
                        xml:id="pg_291"/> from the Inter-American Neutrality Committee has not been
                        received.<note n="47" xml:id="d374fn1">In despatch No. 759, March 5, the
                        Minister in Haiti reported that the communication was received on March 4
                        and the Minister for Foreign Affairs had confirmed his instructions to the
                        Haitian Minister in Washington (740.00111 A.R.–N.C./69).</note> Nevertheless
                    in view of the urgency and in the absence of any objection on the part of the
                    Haitian Government to the competence of the Neutrality Committee to deal with
                    the problems arising from the Declaration at [<hi rend="italic">of</hi>] Panama,
                    he will transmit without delay to the Pan American Union an affirmative reply to
                    the inquiry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
